The family was trapped inside until emergency services arrived, but the two children died before reaching the hospital. JOHANNESBURG - Limpopo police are investigating the deaths of two children who were killed after a petrol bomb was thrown into their home. It's understood the attack happened yesterday morning near Mokopane where the children - aged five and two - were sleeping with their family. The family was trapped inside until emergency services arrived, but the two children died before reaching the hospital. The police's Moatshe Ngoepe said, “The police condemn the brutal attack and subsequent killing of two children in an apparent domestic conflict.”